# LeanCMS Changelog Rule

After **every meaningful change** to this gem, you MUST update `CHANGELOG.md`.

## Format

Follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/) strictly:

```markdown
## [Unreleased]

### Added
- New feature description

### Changed
- Changed behaviour description

### Deprecated
- Deprecated functionality

### Removed
- Removed functionality

### Fixed
- Bug fix description

### Security
- Security fix description
```

## Rules

1. All changes go under `## [Unreleased]` until a version is released.
2. Each entry must be a single, concise sentence on a new bullet line.
3. Use past tense: "Added", "Fixed", "Changed", "Removed", "Deprecated".
4. When a version is released, rename `## [Unreleased]` to `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD` and add a new empty `## [Unreleased]` section at the top.
5. Always update the comparison link at the bottom of the file when releasing.

## What counts as a meaningful change

- New helper methods, model methods, or controller actions
- New content types or CMS settings keys
- Behaviour changes to existing features
- Bug fixes (always document)
- Dependency version changes
- Breaking changes (mark clearly with **BREAKING**)
- New generators or generator templates

## What does NOT need a changelog entry

- Whitespace/formatting fixes
- Comment updates
- Spec changes with no corresponding source change

## Example entry

```markdown
## [Unreleased]

### Added
- `cms_editable_section` and `cms_settings_section` helpers moved from host app into `LeanCms::PageContentHelper`

### Fixed
- `page_content_image_url` no longer raises when ActiveStorage is not configured
```
